event: response.reasoning_summary_text.done
data: {"type":"response.reasoning_summary_text.done","item_id":"rs_05b3f9e989ad3802016a048ca8e0b88193945710ade8f8cd1c","output_index":0,"sequence_number":113,"summary_index":0,"text":"**Calculating distance of Train A**\n\nTrain A travels from 3 pm to 6:10 pm, which is 3 hours and 10 minutes or 3.1667 hours at a speed of 80 km/h. To find the distance, I multiply the time by the speed: 80 km/h times 3.1667 gives me 253.333 km. I could break it down further, showing how 3 hours plus 10 minutes equals 190 minutes, which is also 3.1667 hours. So I conclude that Train A meets at 6:10 pm, 253 1/3 km from Paris."}

