event: response.reasoning_summary_text.done
data: {"type":"response.reasoning_summary_text.done","item_id":"rs_05b3f9e989ad3802016a048ca8e0b88193945710ade8f8cd1c","output_index":0,"sequence_number":221,"summary_index":1,"text":"**Calculating meeting time and distance**\n\nI'm looking at the relative speed of 180 km/h. To find the time, I use the formula: time equals distance divided by speed. So, 390 km divided by 180 km/h gives me 13/6 hours, which is 2 hours and 10 minutes. They meet at 6:10 pm. The distance from Paris can be calculated as 80 times (1 plus 13/6), or simply using 80 times 3 and 1/6, which also gives me 253 1/3 km. I’ll provide units for clarity."}

