data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_05b3f9e989ad3802016a048cb50f3c819397b052cca8a5b8a3","logprobs":[],"output_index":1,"sequence_number":371,"text":"From 3–4 pm only the Paris train runs: distance = 80 km. Remaining gap at 4 pm = 470 − 80 = 390 km.\n\nAfter 4 pm they approach each other at 80 + 100 = 180 km/h. Time to meet = 390 / 180 = 13/6 h = 2 h 10 min.\n\nMeeting time = 4:00 pm + 2 h 10 min = 6:10 pm.\n\nDistance from Paris = distance travelled by Paris train = 80 × (3 + 1/6) h = 80 × 19/6 = 760/3 km = 253 1/3 km."}

